channel.title: AP News - US News
channel.description: Top US News stories from AP News

item.title: US jobless claims jump to 258,000, the most in more than a year. Analysts point to Hurricane Helene
item.description: The number of Americans filing for for unemployment benefits last week jumped to their highest level in a year, which analysts are saying is more likely a result of Hurricane Helene than a broader softening in the labor market.

item.title: Delta’s Q3 profit fell below $1 billion after global tech outage led to thousands of cancellations
item.description: Delta Air Lines says third-quarter earnings fell 26% largely because of fallout from a technology outage that caused several thousand canceled flights in July.

item.title: Tesla is unveiling its long-awaited robotaxi amid doubts about the technology it runs on
item.description: Expectations are high for Tesla’s long-awaited robotaxi unveiling at a Hollywood studio Thursday night. Too high for some analysts and investors.
